{"id":"stones-precious","term":"Stones, Precious","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Frequently referred to (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 10:2\">1 Kings 10:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 3:6\">2 Chr. 3:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 9:10\">9:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 18:16\">Rev. 18:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 21:19\">21:19</a>). There are about twenty different names of such stones in the Bible. They are figuratively introduced to denote value, beauty, durability (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 5:14\">Cant. 5:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 54:11\">Isa 54:11</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 54:12\">12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Lamentations 4:7\">Lam. 4:7</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Kings 10:2","2 Chronicles 3:6","2 Chronicles 9:10","Revelation 18:16","Revelation 21:19","Song of Solomon 5:14","Isaiah 54:11","Isaiah 54:12","Lamentations 4:7"]}